 Further, the higher income differences seem to encourage both poor and
 rich participants to engage in status competitions while high participation
 costs discourage the participation from the poor participant.
 On similar lines with 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "hopkinsWhichInequality2010"
literal "false"

\end_inset

, the chapter contrasts equity in income (rewards) against equity in opportunity
 in the context of status competitions.
